Planning to explore existing projects, and as far as possible combine / extend their techniques and tools for geo-locative sound, for use in Performigrations.  Some projects targeted are:

* [[AudioMobile|http://audio-mobile.org/about#3/25.54/-73.58]]
* [[Stories Matter|http://storytelling.concordia.ca/storiesmatter/]]
* work by [[Locus Sonus|http://locusonus.org/]]. 

Possible platform for developing a globe-browsing map can be cesium (http://cesiumjs.org/),  based on ~WebGl/d3js.  Related links: 

* http://d3js.org/
* Example of globe-map with interactive info-graphics: http://cgi-interactive.clintonfoundation.org/topics?year=ALL
* Temperature anomalies in world climate over the years: http://philogb.github.io/page/temperature-anomalies/
* Other ~WebGL examples: http://www.chromeexperiments.com/webgl
* Also: United Nations Development Programme: http://open.undp.org/#2014

